    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Kyle Tucker** (74.27) stands as our premier offensive anchor. Facing a favorable 4.41 xERA arm in May and benefiting from an outfield wind blowing out, his power-speed profile is perfectly positioned for a ceiling performance. **Drake Baldwin** (71.77) also registers as an elite start; he draws a soft matchup against Freeland and provides exceptional value from the number two hole. While the middle infield trio of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Jacob Wilson**, and **Sam Antonacci** hover near the 60-point threshold, they remain high-upside plays despite varying degrees of SP skill resistance. **Josh Lowe** (64.99) is an essential start today; even with a slight negative adjustment for a high-efficiency opposing catcher, his ability to capitalize on the 4.31 xERA of Holmes makes him a high-floor asset in our critical SB category.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved choosing between **Andy Pages** and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (53.50). While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** possesses a strong xwOBA, the optimizer favored **Andy Pages** due to superior park-adjusted matchups and the beneficial wind conditions that boost his HR potential. We are proceeding cautiously with **Coby Mayo** (54.32), who faces a tough assignment against Fried; while the wind is a slight positive, the presence of an elite hold-pitcher necessitates a tempered expectation for his SB output. Monitor the lineup status for **Heliot Ramos**, as his lower 51.70 score suggests he is on the periphery of our daily utility requirements. With **Luis Robert Jr.** still sidelined on the IL, we continue to rely on our active roster to maintain our competitive edge in the 5x5 standings.",
